result.execSummary:
The defendant Daemon P Hassler #626883 was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Determinate sentence: total 10 years (IC 5 years forthwith DCI, eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program and Substance Abuse Program AFTER 18 months IC, court grants 357 days jail credit on this case)(ES-Extended Supervision 5 years)
Concurrent with: with each count & CONCURRENT with Oconto Co case 14CF26

superMiscConds.notes: as agreed to on all counts including read-ins & Marinette Co consolidation: court orders total $15,627.66 Joint/Several plus 5% & 10% restitution surcharge total $18,049.95 (see attached) due while incarcerated & while on ES.
court orders defendant obtain or maintain full time employment of part time employment if enrolled in school.

court orders No contact with co-defendants Dustin Elliott, Phillip Giese, Kyle Davis or Shannon Westphal.  court orders No contact with any of the victims in Oconto & Marinette Co or their families and residences.

court orders Absolute sobriety (No possession, purchase, consumption any alcohol, illegal drugs, controlled substances, drug paraphernalia without valid prescriptions).  court orders AODA & comply with any & all recommended treatment. Enter into, participate in & successfully complete any other assessments, evaluations and/or treatment programs as directed by DOC agent.
